post_cb({"15783662": {"ParentId": "15783525", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>Paragraph 18.3.2.4 of the C++11 Standard specifies:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_0\"><code>static constexpr T min() noexcept</code>;</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_1\">1 Minimum finite value.</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_2\">2 For floating types with denormalization, returns the minimum positive normalized value.</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_3\">3 Meaningful for all specializations</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_4\">[...]</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_5\"><code>static constexpr T lowest() noexcept</code>;</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_6\">6 A finite value x such that there is no other finite value y where y &lt; x.</p>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_7\">7 Meaningful for all specializations in which is_bounded != false.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Footnote 197 then adds the relevant remark:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_15783525_15783662_8\"><code>lowest()</code> is necessary because not all floating-point representations have a smallest (most negative) value that is the\n  negative of the largest (most positive) finite value.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1932150", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "15783662", "Score": "14", "CreationDate": "2013-04-03T09:30:53.360", "LastActivityDate": "2013-04-03T09:30:53.360"}, "15783596": {"ParentId": "15783525", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>If you check a reference of these functions, e.g. <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/numeric_limits/min\" rel=\"nofollow\">this one for <code>min</code></a> and <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/numeric_limits/lowest\" rel=\"nofollow\">this one for <code>lowest</code></a> you can see that there are some values that differ.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "440558", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "15783596", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2013-04-03T09:28:41.283", "LastActivityDate": "2013-04-03T09:28:41.283"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_15783525_15783662_8": {"section_id": 6724, "quality": 0.9411764705882353, "length": 16}, "so_15783525_15783662_6": {"section_id": 6724, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}, "so_15783525_15783662_7": {"section_id": 6721, "quality": 1.0, "length": 5}, "so_15783525_15783662_2": {"section_id": 6720, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "length": 8}, "so_15783525_15783662_5": {"section_id": 6723, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_15783525_15783662_8": {"section_id": 6479, "quality": 0.9411764705882353, "length": 16}, "so_15783525_15783662_6": {"section_id": 6479, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}, "so_15783525_15783662_7": {"section_id": 6476, "quality": 1.0, "length": 5}, "so_15783525_15783662_2": {"section_id": 6475, "quality": 0.8888888888888888, "length": 8}, "so_15783525_15783662_5": {"section_id": 6478, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_15783525_15783662_8": {"section_id": 8218, "quality": 0.9411764705882353, "length": 16}, "so_15783525_15783662_2": {"section_id": 8214, "quality": 0.7777777777777778, "length": 7}, "so_15783525_15783662_5": {"section_id": 8217, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}, "so_15783525_15783662_7": {"section_id": 8215, "quality": 1.0, "length": 5}, "so_15783525_15783662_0": {"section_id": 8212, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}, "so_15783525_15783662_6": {"section_id": 8218, "quality": 1.0, "length": 8}}}, "15783651": {"ParentId": "15783525", "LastEditDate": "2013-04-03T14:19:26.113", "CommentCount": "2", "CreationDate": "2013-04-03T09:30:31.960", "OwnerUserId": "542190", "LastEditorUserId": "542190", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "15783651", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>For floating point types <code>min</code> returns the smallest finite number that is <code>&gt; 0</code> representable in the type (i.e. the number having the lowest absolute value <code>!= 0</code>) while <code>lowest</code> returns the smallest finite number that is representable (i.e. the negative number of maximal absolute value that is less than <code>-infinity</code>).</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-04-03T14:19:26.113"}, "15783525": {"CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-04-03T09:25:57.930", "PostTypeId": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "15783662", "LastEditorUserId": "1932150", "LastActivityDate": "2013-04-03T14:19:26.113", "LastEditDate": "2013-04-03T09:34:10.110", "ViewCount": "2165", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "numeric_limits lowest and min member functions", "Id": "15783525", "Score": "12", "Body": "<pre><code>numeric_limits&lt;T&gt;::min();\nnumeric_limits&lt;T&gt;::lowest();\n</code></pre>\n<p>What is the different between the value returned by both functions?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><stl><standard-library>", "OwnerUserId": "235860", "AnswerCount": "3"}});